git clone --recursive https://github.com/NOAA-PSL/global-workflow
cd global-workflow
git checkout 3dvar_coupledreanl_scoutrun
git submodule update --init --recursive --remote
source dev/ush/gw_setup.sh
cd sorc
./build_all.sh gfs gsi gdas &> build_all.out
sh linkworkflow.sh
cd ..
pslot="C192coupled3dvar_test" RUNTESTS="/gpfs/f6/ira-da/scratch/$USER/GWTESTS" ICSDIR_ROOT="/gpfs/f6/ira-da/proj-shared/Jeffrey.S.Whitaker/replayics/C192mx025" HPC_ACCOUNT="ira-da" ./dev/workflow/create_experiment.py --yaml dev/ci/cases/coupledreanl/C192mx025_3DVarAOWCDA.yaml

on orion/hercules:
pslot="C192coupled3dvar_test" RUNTESTS="/work2/noaa/gsienkf/$USER/GWTESTS" ICSDIR_ROOT="/work/noaa/gsienkf/whitaker/replayics/replayics/C192mx025" HPC_ACCOUNT="gsienkf" ./dev/workflow/create_experiment.py --yaml dev/ci/cases/coupledreanl/C192mx025_3DVarAOWCDA.yaml

cd to EXPDIR
run rocotorun -w $PSLOT.xml -d $PSLOT.db
scrontab $PSLOT.crontab
ln -fs $HOMEGFS/dev/workflow/rocoto_viewer.py .
run ./rocoto_viewer.py -w $PSLOT.xml -d $PSLOT.db to monitor progress

NOTES:

log files go to $RUNTESTS/COMROOT/$EXPDIR/logs. if rocotoviewer shows a workflow step died, look in the log file here to find the error message.

if BUILD_GSINFO=YES, versions/fix.ver needs to be edited to point to an updated gsi fix dir with the build_gsinfo submodule included.
AND sorc/link_workflow.sh needs to be edited so that the new gsi fix dir is linked (+"gaeac6") FIX_DIR="/gpfs/f6/ira-da/world-shared/global/glopara/fix" ;;)

To monitor t2m/q2m obs, add

  t2m       1      -1         2m_temperature       tmp2m
  q2m       1      -1         2m_spec_humidity     spfh2m

to met_guess:: in anavinfo, and

 t2m       1      0     met_guess    t2m
 q2m       1      0     met_guess    q2m

